
<h1>Project README</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
    This project is a console-based RPG (Role-Playing Game) application developed in C++. 
    It allows players to navigate through various screens, manage their inventory, 
    and engage with game elements such as items and characters. 
    The primary focus of the game is to create an immersive experience where players 
    can interact with their environment, utilize items, and progress through different stages of gameplay.
</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Player Management:</strong> The game allows players to create and manage a character, 
        including initializing their inventory with various items like weapons and health potions.</li>
    <li><strong>Inventory System:</strong> Players can manage their items through an inventory system, 
        where they can send items to a belt, use consumable items, or discard unwanted items.</li>
    <li><strong>Screen Navigation:</strong> The application features multiple screens, such as the 
        starting screen and player status screen, enabling players to navigate through different stages of the game easily.</li>
    <li><strong>Dynamic Item Usage:</strong> Players can use items from their inventory, enhancing their character's abilities or health as they progress.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Structure</h2>
<p>The project is organized into several directories:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Screens:</strong> Contains screen classes responsible for rendering different parts of the game.</li>
    <li><strong>Entities:</strong> Contains classes that represent various game elements such as players and items.</li>
    <li><strong>Utils:</strong> Contains utility functions and classes for list management and string operations.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Main Components</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Player:</strong> Represents the player character, managing attributes and inventory.</li>
    <li><strong>Item:</strong> Represents items that can be collected, used, or discarded.</li>
    <li><strong>Backpack and Belt:</strong> Data structures used to manage the player's inventory and equipped items.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Run</h2>
<p>To run the project, simply execute the <code>setup.bat</code> file, which will compile the code and start the application.</p>

<h2>Contributing</h2>
<p>Contributions are welcome! If you have ideas for features, improvements, or bug fixes, 
please feel free to submit a pull request or open an issue.</p>

